to the editor the democrats problem goes deeper than george packer suggests op ed april 6 it is not a matter of regaining their voices on a principle equality can no longer cut it we are not born with equal endowments we are not equally deserving in terms of hard work and we do n't start with equal access to opportunities a stronger case can be made for fair shares a sense of fairness is an evolved predisposition in humans and that is what the very wealthy violate why should they care it 's in their self interest great disparities of wealth coupled with severe deprivation for the disadvantaged are the seeds and the soil in which reform movements and revolutions grow peter a corning palo alto calif april 6 2001

